docs\reviews\synthetic-playtest\2026-04-27\design-8\raw\codex.md:1:1. Medium – the ordering assertions target the wrong recorded-command field. In `docs/design/2026-04-27-synthetic-playtest-harness-design.md` §6.4, §12, and ADR 6, the spec says to verify `bundle.commands[].submissionSequence`. The current bundle schema exposes `RecordedCommand.sequence` in `src/session-bundle.ts:41-46`; `submissionSequence` exists on `CommandExecutionResult` in `src/world.ts:145-153`, not on recorded commands. As written, the composition guidance and acceptance criteria point at a nonexistent property, which could either produce broken tests/docs or force an unnecessary schema change to an already-shipped session-recording type. Those spots should say `bundle.commands[].sequence` if the intent is submission ordering, or `bundle.executions[].submissionSequence` if the intent is execution linkage.
